      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "not",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " obtain the promise, [",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μὴ λαβόντες τὰς ἐπαγγελίας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 11:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "οὐκ ἐκομίσαντο τὴν ἐπαγγελίαν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 11:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "], but could only wave his hand to it and salute it at a distance, yet the initial fulfilment he did see and was compensated for all his waiting by seeing the beginnings of that great history which ran on to the consummate performance of the promise in Christ. Bleek and Rendall understand by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐπέτυχε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " … “obtained from God a promise of future blessing,” and not the thing itself. But in this case ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μακροθυμήσας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " would be irrelevant. He had not to wait for the promise, but for its fulfilment.",
